princeton_ansible.title: Adds a role for studio processing
Upgrade nodejs for orangelight, enable controlled upgrades generally

comments.body:
We can see the base version number now, but the `apt` task still fails, saying no version matches. The playbook should probably:
- check the installed version
- if the installed version matches the desired version, stop there
- if the installed version does not match the desired version, download node from `nodejs.org/download/release/latest-v{{ desired_version }}.x/node-v{{ desired_version }}."whatever comes next"-linux-x64.tar.gz`, then unzip and install node from that . . . but I'm not sure how to do the matching in a sustainable way (meaning, a way that works now for 16.14.0 and will still work when 16.20.8 comes out); alternatively, we could update the node version to be more specific (for example, 16.14.0 instead of 16.x)

@carolyncole the same construction shows up in groups_vars/orangelight/qa.yml [here](https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/blob/519597fdfdc27853a490e2438e77769965fec4ff/group_vars/orangelight/qa.yml#L2) and also [here](https://github.com/pulibrary/princeton_ansible/blob/519597fdfdc27853a490e2438e77769965fec4ff/group_vars/orangelight/qa.yml#L45). Do we want to update those too?
